8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 789, L.D. 1184, “An Act to Require
9 Municipal Reporting on Residential Building Permits, Dwelling Units Permitted and
10 Demolished and Certificates of Occupancy Issued”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §3241, sub-§2, ¶C is enacted to read:
14 C. The office shall assist a municipality with 4,000 or more residents in meeting the
15 requirements of subsection 5. The assistance must include reimbursement of 90% of
16 actual expenses incurred by a municipality if collection or reporting of data as required
17 by subsection 5 is a modification or expansion of municipal activities so as to
18 necessitate additional expenditures from local revenues.
19 Sec. 2. 5 MRSA §3241, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
20 5. Municipal housing data reporting. By January 31st of each year, a municipality
21 with 4,000 or more residents shall provide to the office for use in administering the program
22 an annual report of:
23 A. Residential building permit applications, including the number of applications
24 submitted, approved and denied, categorized into single-family, single-family with
25 accessory dwelling unit, 2-to-4-family and more-than-4-family homes;
26 B. The number of dwelling units permitted and demolished; and
27 C. The number of certificates of occupancy or other final approvals of housing units
28 issued, the number of those housing units affordable to persons or families whose
29 incomes are 80% or less of the area median income as determined by the Maine State
30 Housing Authority and the number of those housing units affordable to persons or
31 families whose incomes are from 81% to 120% of the area median income as
32 determined by the Maine State Housing Authority.
33 As used in this subsection, "accessory dwelling unit" has the same meaning as in Title
34 30-A, section 4301, subsection 1-C.
35 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
36 allocations are made.
